\begin_layout Standard
Ulrey did some of the first experimental work to verify the Duane-Hunt law
 and also to check on the difference of Z on the energy distribution of
 bremsstrahlung.
 He used an X-ray tube with separate plates of different composition on
 each of different hexagonal faces.
 The voltage was generated by a step up transformer and varied up to 
\begin_inset Formula $50\,\mathrm{kV}$
\end_inset

, and an ionization chamber filled with 
\begin_inset Formula $\ce{C_{2}H_{5}Br}$
\end_inset

 vapor was used to measure the energies of the emitted X-rays.
