\begin_layout Standard
Unfortunately, even with almost 100 years between the original work on these
 spectra and now, most of the current work done is still experimental.
 This is largely due to the effect that screening has upon the energy transfer
 to the electromagnetic particle.
 Bethe's work clearly stated that, while it is possible to theoretically
 solve the energy transfer for a free particle in a single field, in reality
 there is some amount of screening done by other electrons in the material.
 It is still unknown as to what amount that modifies the apparent field
 working upon the incident particle.
